sum(h.null_cnt) nnv, sum(h.avgcln * t.rowcnt)/greatest(:total_rows, 1) avgcln, min(nvl2(h.lowval, h.minimum, null)) nmin, -- normalized min max(nvl2(h.hival, h.maximum, null)) nmax, -- normalized max min(h.lowval) minval, -- raw value max(h.hival) maxval from sys.tabcompart$ t, sys.hist_head$ h where t.bo# = :tab_num and t.obj# = h.obj# group by h.intcol# ) b, ( -- global ndv of a column = # of hashvalues in global synopsis * -- (2 ^ split) select /*+ no_merge use_hash(sb s) */ sb.intcol#, count(distinct(s.hashvalue)) * max(sb.maxsplit) ndv -- min(sb.maxsplit) or max(sb.maxsplit) does not matter here -- one sb.intcol# is uniquely associated with one sb.maxsplit from (-- for each column, this view gets maximal split level among -- its partition synopses in the table. -- It also returns a column splitmask which is a hashvalue. -- This hashvalue is n 1's where n is the splitting level select /*+ no_merge */ t.intcol#, power(2, max(split)) maxsplit from sys.wri$_optstat_synopsis_head$ t where t.bo# = :tab_num group by t.intcol# ) sb, sys.wri$_optstat_synopsis$ s where s.bo# = :tab_num and s.intcol# = sb.intcol# and mod(s.hashvalue + 1, sb.maxsplit) = 0 -- keep only synopses on same split level -- i.e., synopses ending with maxsplit 1's -- do not use bitand(s.hashvalue, sb.splitmask) = -- sb.splitmask, bitand does not support ub8 gro up by sb.intcol# ) n where b.intcol# = n.intcol#(+)

Interconnect Ping Latency Stats

  • Ping latency of the roundtrip of a message from this instance to
  • target instances.
  • The target instance is identified by an instance number.
  • Average and standard deviation of ping latency is given in miliseconds
  • for message sizes of 500 bytes and 8K.
  • Note that latency of a message from the instance to itself is used as
  • control, since message latency can include wait for CPU
